  "time_ut": 1660916733,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dda\u0db1 - \u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dd2 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9c UN \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "In a meeting with the Presidents of Ukraine and Turkey",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "United Nations Secretary General Antonio Guterres has met with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky and Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan in the city of Lviv in western Ukraine and held a tripartite discussion.",
        "Issues such as grain export, safety of nuclear power plants and reconstruction of Ukraine were discussed in the meeting.",
        "At a press conference after the meeting, the leaders hailed the success of the UN-brokered agreement allowing ships to pass through three Ukrainian Black Sea ports, and said they discussed ways to improve the deal.",
        "Guterres said 21 ships left Ukrainian ports in less than a month, and 15 vessels left Istanbul for Ukraine to load grain and other foodstuffs.",
        "Guterres said the signatories to the agreement acted professionally and in good faith to keep the food flowing.",
        "\"Large quantities of food and fertilizer from Ukraine and Russia are critical to further calm commodity markets and lower prices,\" he noted.",
        "Meanwhile, when referring to the security of the Zaporizhzhia nuclear power plant, Guterres said that military equipment and personnel should be withdrawn from the Russian-run nuclear power plant and that the site should be secured.",
        "\"This facility should not be used as part of any military operation. Instead, an agreement is urgently needed to re-establish exclusively civilian infrastructure in Zaporizhzhia and ensure the security of the area,\" Guterres added."
      ],
